e changes. My aim is to make the interactive elements stand out.\n\n\n**Improving Hover Interaction**\n\nI'm now iterating on the hover interaction within the right panel. I am focusing on making the node descriptions more prominent when a user hovers, specifically the animation and content. The goal is a more fluid and informative user experience with animated node descriptions that are clear and well-integrated.\n\n\n**Enhancing Panel Clarity**\n\nI'm now focusing on refining the visual clarity of the video simulator console within the right panel. I'm considering text size adjustments, contrasting colors, and animations for improved readability. I am also investigating the impact on the overall visual flow of information, in addition to the text. The goal is to make the content more easily understood at a glance.\n\n\n**Refactoring Log Display**\n\nI'm now refactoring the log display within the right panel. My aim is to make it more compact and readable, focusing on Tailwind classes for brevity. I'm streamlining the structure, eliminating unnecessary divs, and making the code more semantic. I'm focusing on improved color-coding and better vertical rhythm for log entries. I'm currently assessing the `text-left` alignment to determine if it can be combined with other classes.\n\n\n**Streamlining Button Styling**\n\nI'm now streamlining the styling for the play/pause and reset buttons within the simulator control panel. I'm aiming for greater visual consistency and reduced JSX code. I'm focusing on consolidating shared styles and refining hover effects. Specifically, the goal is to make these changes visually clear while minimizing the amount of code.\n\n\n"}}
